metadata.name: Overgrown house #7 #1/69
metadata.description: I find beauty in old abandoned houses, cracks and scuffs left by time give even more meaning to architecture. Old houses merge with nature year after year, when no man steps into them. Looking at this, you ask yourself questions about the meaning and transience of life, I try to feel every house that I draw, because in the end there will be nothing left of them. Drawing only.
